{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Eljigin |image = |pop = |region1 = {{flagcountry|Mongolia}} |pop1 = 6592 (2010)<ref>[[Demographics of Mongolia#Ethnic groups of Mongolia.5B4.5D|Demographics of Mongolia]]</ref> |languages = Eljigin subdialect of [[Mongolian language|Khalkha Mongolian]] language |religions = [[Tibetan Buddhism]], [[Shamanism]] |related= [[Mongols]], especially [[Khalkha Mongols]] }} The '''Eljigin''' people are a [[Khalkha Mongols|Khalkha Mongolian]] sub-ethnic group. They live in [[Zavhan Province|Zavhan province]].The name sounds similar to Mongolian word "el" for "this" and to Turkic word "[[tegin]]" for "lord"
