The '''Min peoples''' or '''Mountain Ok peoples''' are a cultural group in the [[West Sepik Province]] of [[Papua New Guinea]].<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Moretti|2007|p=306}}</ref><ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Barker|2007|p=28}}</ref>
The Min peoples, though multiple distinct peoples, shared a ritual system.<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Robbins|2004|p=15}}</ref> The [[Telefol people|Telefol]] were acknowledged by the Min as being at the highest level of sacred knowledge, and groups such as the [[Baktaman people|Baktaman]] were at the lowest level. In this ranking the [[Urapmin people|Urapmin]] were either at the top or at least very close to the Telefol.<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|Robbins|2004|p=17}}</ref> This is similar to the caste system used by the Ancient Indians, specific of the Vedic Society.
